dt: {bc}any of a genus ({it}Fagus{/it} of the family Fagaceae, the beech family) of hardwood trees with smooth gray bark and small edible nuts

et: Middle English {it}beche{/it}, from Old English {it}bēce{/it}; akin to Old English {it}bōc{/it} beech, Old High German {it}buohha{/it}, Latin {it}fagus{/it}, Greek {it}phēgos{/it} oak
shortdef: any of a genus (Fagus of the family Fagaceae, the beech family) of hardwood trees with smooth gray bark and small edible nuts; also : its wood

dt: {bc}a beech with shining coppery-red leaves that is a widely planted cultivar of a beech ({it}Fagus sylvatica{/it}) native to Europe

shortdef: a beech with shining coppery-red leaves that is a widely planted cultivar of a beech (Fagus sylvatica) native to Europe
